===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|ja|ヤンデレ|tr=yandere}}, a portmanteau of {{m|ja|病んでる|tr=yanderu}}, contraction of {{m|ja|[[病んで]][[いる]]|tr=yande iru}}, progressive tense of {{m|ja|病む|tr=yamu||to be sick}}, and {{m|ja|デレデレ|tr=dere-dere||in a lovey-dovey, infatuated, or lovestruck manner|pos=adverb}}.<ref>
{{cite-book
|year=2010
|author=Richard W. Kroon
|title=A/V A to Z: An Encyclopedic Dictionary of Media, Entertainment and Other Audiovisual Terms
|publisher=McFarland & Company
|ISBN=9780786457403
|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=HjmNAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA760&dq=%22yandere%22
|page=760
}}</ref><ref>{{cite-web|url=http://www.japanesewithanime.com/2016/07/tsundere-kuudere-yandere-meaning.html|title=Tsundere, Yandere, Kuudere, Dandere - Meaning|site=Japanese with Anime|section=Yandere ヤンデレ|sectionurl=http://www.japanesewithanime.com/2016/07/tsundere-kuudere-yandere-meaning.html#yandere-meaning|date=21 July 2016}}
</ref>
<br/>Developed on the model of {{m|en|tsundere||being cold and even hostile towards another person before gradually showing a warm and caring side over time}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈjɑːndɛɹeɪ/}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|chiefly|Japanese fiction}} A [[character]], usually a [[girl]], who has a [[obsessive]] and [[possessive]] side in regards to their [[crush]], ready to use [[violent]] and [[murderous]] [[mean]]s to [[maintain]] an [[exclusive]] [[bond]].
